                            <comment id="13712002" author="swapnilghike" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2013 04:23:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Sriram, can you explain what we are trying to achieve here? I am not sure if I understood the meaning of &quot;jitter&quot; completely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13712481" author="guozhang" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2013 16:53:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-615&quot; title=&quot;Avoid fsync on log segment roll&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-615&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-615&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; would resolve this issue eventually, but I agree that adding a jitter (I am guessing it means adding a random shift for time based rolling policy) is a quick solution for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13942375" author="jkreps" created="Thu, 20 Mar 2014 22:00:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-615&quot; title=&quot;Avoid fsync on log segment roll&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-615&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-615&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; isn&apos;t quite suffient. We still do fsync on log roll it just is done asynchronously. So if you have 1000 partitions and they all roll due to time-based roll you still get a kind of I/O storm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14170196" author="ewencp" created="Mon, 13 Oct 2014 23:16:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/26663/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/26663/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
